{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"283b1674-12d8-49de-a2e3-f8895ea9ab1a","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"0.6.1\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Set the output type** to `Exe` in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run\n   ```\n   Or continue using `dotnet test` (which auto-detects MTP projects).\n\nThat's it. The `xunit.runner.mtp` package wires up xUnit to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Your test code stays the same — no source changes needed.\n\n> **Note:** `xunit.runner.mtp` 0.6.x targets xunit v2 (2.9.x). Check [NuGet](https://www.nuget.org/packages/xunit.runner.mtp) for the latest compatible version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a18b0ae0-17a9-4dfb-bbb4-5eb484a118a7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"E3EA:3D936D:15DEF1D:18767B2:6A051F52"},"id":"649f53b7-fc07-4797-baca-e550f882a5f1","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:23.277Z","parentId":"723b7a3c-12df-4a48-acfd-8274a0a252e0"}
